    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-03T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-03T06:00:00-05:00" n="4"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890b.6363 Gulf Oil Corporation/21: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain (<persName corresp="#p_AR1"
                            type="from">Atherton</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-03T11:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 3, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 3—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>45. Department’s 50, February 2, 1 p.m. On January 27 <persName corresp="#p_OSL1"
                        >Oliphant</persName> telephoned me Foreign Office were pushing matter to
                    their utmost ability, and on February 1 by appointment I called on <persName
                        corresp="#p_OSL1">Oliphant</persName> at the Foreign Office who informed me
                    Foreign Office had called conference on January 29 of interested departments
                    concerned.</p>
                <p>I understand confidentially Colonial Office deliberations are completed but
                    Indian Government have not yet decided their position, and urgent telegram has
                    been sent pointing out the undue delay.</p>
                <p>I have kept <persName corresp="#p_DMH1">Major Davis</persName>, Gulf Company
                    representative here, fully informed from day to day.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_AR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Atherton</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
